headline.main: ITALY BREAKS OFF BRITISH SHIP DEAL; BRITISH WARSHIP SUNK BY GERMANS OFF NORWAY

lead_paragraph: LONDON, May 31--Italy, it was learned tonight, has made another unfriendly gesture toward Britain by suddenly breaking off negotiations for an agreement on the troublesome problem of contraband control in the Mediterranean, which a few days ago was believed here to have been solved.
